org.opendaylight.controller.md.sal.dom.broker.impl

Interface DOMDataCommitExecutor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DOMConcurrentDataCommitCoordinator, DOMDataCommitCoordinatorImpl

    public interface DOMDataCommitExecutor
    Executor of Three Phase Commit coordination for DOMDataWriteTransaction transactions. Implementations are responsible for executing implementation of three-phase commit protocol on supplied DOMStoreThreePhaseCommitCohorts.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      com.google.common.util.concurrent.CheckedFuture<java.lang.Void,TransactionCommitFailedException> submit(DOMDataWriteTransaction tx, java.lang.Iterable<DOMStoreThreePhaseCommitCohort> cohort)
      Submits supplied transaction to be executed in context of provided cohorts.

    • Method Detail

      • submit

        com.google.common.util.concurrent.CheckedFuture<java.lang.Void,TransactionCommitFailedException> submit(DOMDataWriteTransaction tx,
                                                                                                      java.lang.Iterable<DOMStoreThreePhaseCommitCohort> cohort)
        Submits supplied transaction to be executed in context of provided cohorts. Transaction is used only as a context, cohorts should be associated with this transaction.
        Parameters:
        tx - Transaction to be used as context for reporting
        cohort - DOM Store cohorts representing provided transaction, its subtransactions.
        Returns:
        a CheckedFuture. if commit coordination on cohorts finished successfully, nothing is returned from the Future, On failure, the Future fails with a TransactionCommitFailedException.
